caption:
Congratulations on your fake promotion!

I remember way back in the early '00s being asked to work on a really important project important to the company's relationship with Microsoft on a special small team with the software architect. I'd have to come in on Saturdays, but they wouldn't ask me to do it if they didn't trust me to do it. They sent an email announcing it, like I had won an award.

Reader, I did it, and it started me on the Road to Burnout.
